Moreover, the optical properties of both solutions and thin films were investigated by UV–Vis as well as fluorescence spectroscopy. Both acceptors have their solution absorption maximum located around 530 nm (Fig. 2a), with the molar absorption coefficients of 9.2 × 104 dm3 mol−1 cm−1 in both cases (Table 2). Also, both compounds exhibit a second absorption peak at shorter wavelength (507 nm). The first absorption peak is a HOMO–LUMO transition (Table 1 in DFT section) and has a charge transfer character (from the linker to perylene monoimide). The second absorption peak is a HOMO-1 to LUMO + 1 transition, which can be identified as a locally excited state on the perylene monoimide (see the MO electron density changes in Fig. 1b).Fig. 2
